<title>MEXICO: Ahmsa gives 22 pct wage hike - Notimex.</title>
<headline>Ahmsa gives 22 pct wage hike - Notimex.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-05-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican steel company Altos Hornos de Mexico SA (Ahmsa) workers received a 22 percent pay raise and increased benefits, state news agency Notimex reported late Sunday.</p>
<p>Regional union leader Julian Torres said the raise for approximately 2,500 workers avoided a strike scheduled to begin on Monday.  The pay hike would be effective as of May 1, Torres said.</p>
<p>Workers at steel plant number one accepted an 18 percent wage hike in March, also avoiding a threatened strike.</p>
<p>Mexico's inflation this year is expected to fall to 15 to 20 percent from 27.7 percent in 1997.</p>
<p>((--Timna Tanners, Mexico City newsroom +525 728-7903))</p>
